\begin_layout Subsection
The Absence of Controlled Invariance
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Suppose,
 to the contrary,
 that there exists a function 
\begin_inset Formula $h:C^{2}\left(\mathbb{R}^{3}\to\mathbb{R}^{2}\right)$
\end_inset

 satisfying the conditions:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Formula $h\left(q_{*}\left(t\right)\right)\equiv0$
\end_inset

 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Formula $\mathrm{rank}\,dh\left(q\right)=2$
\end_inset

 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $q$
\end_inset

 from 
\begin_inset Formula $h^{-1}\left(0\right)$
\end_inset

,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
the set
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\Gamma\equiv\left\{ \left(q,\dot{q}\right)\in\mathbb{R}^{6}\mid h\left(q\right)=0\,\text{and}\,L_{\dot{q}}h\left(q\right)=0\right\} 
\]

\end_inset

 is a controlled invariant manifold.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As discussed in
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Consolini-2018"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 the set 
\begin_inset Formula $\Gamma$
\end_inset

,
 is a manifold of dimension two,
 provided that 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathrm{rank}\,dh\left(q\right)=2$
\end_inset

.
 This manifold represents the tangent bundle 
\begin_inset Formula $\Gamma=T\mathcal{C}$
\end_inset

,
 where the base space 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{C}$
\end_inset

 is given by 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{C}=\left\{ q\in\mathbb{R}^{3}\mid\exists\,t:q=q_{*}\left(t\right)\right\} ,$
\end_inset

 which corresponds to the image of the trajectory 
\begin_inset Formula $q_{*}\left(t\right)$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To demonstrate the controlled invariance of 
\begin_inset Formula $\Gamma$
\end_inset

,
 we analyze the dynamics of the variable 
\begin_inset Formula $y=h\left(q\right)$
\end_inset

,
 which are given by 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
\dot{y} & =L_{\dot{q}}h\left(q\right)\nonumber \\
\ddot{y} & =dh\left(q\right)\left(B\left(q\right)u-G\right)+L_{\dot{q}}^{2}h\left(q\right).\label{eq:ddot_y}
\end{align}

\end_inset

According to
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
after "Chapter 6"
key "Isidori-1995"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 the set 
\begin_inset Formula $\Gamma$
\end_inset

 is controlled invariant if and only if for every 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(q,\dot{q}\right)\in\Gamma$
\end_inset

,
 there exists a smooth mapping 
\begin_inset Formula $u:\Gamma\to\mathbb{R}^{2}$
\end_inset

 such that the right hand side of the equation
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:ddot_y"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 is identically zero.
 This implies,
 that the following system of linear algebraic equations in 
\begin_inset Formula $u$
\end_inset

 must be solvable for all 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(q,\dot{q}\right)\in\Gamma$
\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
dh\left(q\right)B\left(q\right)u=dh\left(q\right)G-L_{\dot{q}}^{2}h\left(q\right).\label{eq:linsys-for-u}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

Here,
 two options are possible:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $dh\left(q\right)B\left(q\right)$
\end_inset

 is of full rank.
 In this case,
 
\begin_inset Formula $\Gamma$
\end_inset

 is controlled invariant for any bounded right-hand side.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
If the matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $dh\left(q\right)B\left(q\right)$
\end_inset

 is not of full rank for some 
\begin_inset Formula $q_{0}\in\mathcal{C}$
\end_inset

,
 then there exists a nontrivial row vector 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula $Ndh\left(q\right)B\left(q\right)=0$
\end_inset

.
 In this case,
 the necessary condition of controlled invariance becomes
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
Ndh\left(q_{0}\right)G-NL_{\dot{q}}^{2}h\left(q_{0}\right)=0\quad\text{for all}\quad\dot{q}\in T_{q_{0}}\mathcal{C}.\label{eq:dq_constr}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

Importantly,
 the first term 
\begin_inset Formula $Ndh\left(q_{0}\right)G$
\end_inset

 does not depend on 
\begin_inset Formula $\dot{q}$
\end_inset

,
 while the second is bilinear in 
\begin_inset Formula $\dot{q}$
\end_inset

.
 This implies,
 that the only option to satisfy condition
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:dq_constr"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 is for both terms to vanish:
 
\begin_inset Formula $Ndh\left(q_{0}\right)G=0$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $NL_{\dot{q}}^{2}h\left(q_{0}\right)=0$
\end_inset

 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $\dot{q}\in T_{q_{0}}\mathcal{C}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let us consider the point 
\begin_inset Formula $q_{0}\in\mathcal{C}$
\end_inset

 given by:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
q_{0}=q_{*}\left(0\right)=\left(0,0,\frac{\pi}{2}\right)^{\top}.
\]

\end_inset

At this point the velocity vector 
\begin_inset Formula $\dot{q}_{0}=\dot{q}_{*}\left(0\right)=\left(1,0,-2\right)^{\top}\in T_{q_{0}}\mathcal{C}$
\end_inset

 lies in the image of the matrix
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
B\left(q_{0}\right) & =\left(\begin{array}{cc}
-1 & 0\\
0 & 0\\
0 & 1
\end{array}\right),
\end{align*}

\end_inset

i.e.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\dot{q}_{0}\in\mathrm{Im}\left[B\left(q_{0}\right)\right]$
\end_inset

.
 The condition 
\begin_inset Formula $h\left(q_{*}\left(t\right)\right)\equiv0$
\end_inset

 implies that the rows of 
\begin_inset Formula $dh\left(q_{0}\right)$
\end_inset

 are orthogonal to 
\begin_inset Formula $\dot{q}_{0}$
\end_inset

,
 i.e.,
 
\begin_inset Formula $dh\left(q_{0}\right)\dot{q}_{0}=0$
\end_inset

.
 Consequently,
 the matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $dh\left(q_{0}\right)B\left(q_{0}\right)$
\end_inset

 cannot have full rank.
 This implies the exstence of a row vector 
\begin_inset Formula $N\in\mathbb{R}^{1\times2}\backslash\left\{ 0\right\} $
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula $Ndh\left(q_{0}\right)B\left(q_{0}\right)=0$
\end_inset

.
 Then,
 in order for 
\begin_inset Formula $\Gamma$
\end_inset

 to be controlled invariant,
 the condition
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:dq_constr"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 must be satisfied.
 Since the matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $dh\left(q\right)$
\end_inset

 consists two of linear independent rows,
 the row vector 
\begin_inset Formula $Ndh\left(q_{0}\right)\in\mathbb{R}^{1\times3}$
\end_inset

 is nonzero.
 Furthermore,
 the orthogonal complement of this row vector is a two-dimensional linear space that coincides with 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathrm{Im}\left[B\left(q_{0}\right)\right]$
\end_inset

.
 Observing that the vector 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

 does not lie in 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathrm{Im}\left[B\left(q_{0}\right)\right]$
\end_inset

,
 we conclude that 
\begin_inset Formula $Ndh\left(q_{0}\right)G$
\end_inset

 is nonzero.
 Therefore,
 the equation
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:dq_constr"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 can only hold for specific values of 
\begin_inset Formula $\dot{q}$
\end_inset

,
 which are 
\begin_inset Formula $\dot{q}=\pm\dot{q}_{0}$
\end_inset

.
 However,
 if we consider 
\begin_inset Formula $\dot{q}=0\in T_{q_{0}}\mathcal{Q}$
\end_inset

,
 then the second term becomes zero and the equality
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:dq_constr"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 violates.
 This contradicts the requirement that the equaility
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:dq_constr"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 must hold for all 
\begin_inset Formula $\dot{q}$
\end_inset

 from the tangent space 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{q_{0}}\mathcal{Q}$
\end_inset

.
 Therefore,
 we conclude that the set 
\begin_inset Formula $\Gamma$
\end_inset

 is 
\series bold
not a controlled invariant manifold
\series default
.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This general result can also be verified by the reader through direct computation using a specific candidate VHC,
 such as 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
