 but rather a typical example within a broad class of admitable solutions.
 To this end,
 we briefly remind the mothod of motions planning based on VHCs
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Shiriaev-2005-constructive-tool,Shiriaev-2006-periodic-planning"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 As known,
 according to 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
after "Proposition 2"
key "Shiriaev-2005-constructive-tool"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 dynamics of 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:lag-sys"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 with imposed VHC 
\begin_inset Formula $q=\phi\left(\theta\right)$
\end_inset

 are determined by the equation
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\alpha\left(\theta\right)\ddot{\theta}+\beta\left(\theta\right)\dot{\theta}^{2}+\gamma\left(\theta\right)=0\label{eq:alpha-beta-gamma}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where the scalar coefficients 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha\left(\theta\right),\beta\left(\theta\right)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma\left(\theta\right)$
\end_inset

 are defined as
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\alpha\left(\theta\right) & =B_{\perp}\left(\phi\left(\theta\right)\right)M\left(\phi\left(\theta\right)\right)\phi'\left(\theta\right),\\
\beta\left(\theta\right) & =B_{\perp}\left(\phi\left(\theta\right)\right)M\left(\phi\left(\theta\right)\right)\phi''\left(\theta\right)\\
 & \quad+B_{\perp}\left(\phi\left(\theta\right)\right)C\left(\phi\left(\theta\right),\phi'\left(\theta\right)\right)\phi'\left(\theta\right),\\
\gamma\left(\theta\right) & =B_{\perp}\left(\phi\left(\theta\right)\right)G\left(\phi\left(\theta\right)\right)
\end{align*}

\end_inset

and matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $B_{\perp}\left(q\right)\in\mathbb{R}^{1\times n}\backslash\left\{ 0\right\} $
\end_inset

 is a left annihilator of 
\begin_inset Formula $B\left(q\right)$
\end_inset

.
 For the PVTOL system in section above,
 we used the VHC
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\phi\left(\theta\right)=\left(\theta,-\frac{1}{2}\theta^{2},\frac{\pi}{2}-\arctan2\theta\right)^{\top}\label{eq:pvtol-vhc}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

and matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $B_{\perp}\left(q\right)=\left(\cos\psi,\sin\psi,0\right)$
\end_inset

,
 which result in the reduced dynamics:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\theta\ddot{\theta}-\dot{\theta}^{2}+1=0.\label{eq:pvtol-reduced-dynamics}
\end{equation}

