\begin_inset Formula $\Gamma$
\end_inset

 associated with a non-regular VHC 
\begin_inset Formula $q=\phi\left(\theta\right)$
\end_inset

 loses controlled invariance at the configuration 
\begin_inset Formula $q_{s}=\phi\left(\theta_{s}\right)$
\end_inset

 corresponding to the singularity 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{s}$
\end_inset

.
 This loss follows from Theorem
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "thm:singular-solutions-existence"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

,
 which states that any solution passing through 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{s}$
\end_inset

 must have the specific velocity 
\begin_inset Formula $\dot{\theta}_{s}=\pm\sqrt{-\gamma\left(\theta_{s}\right)/\beta\left(\theta_{s}\right)}$
\end_inset

.
 Consequently,
 at the configuration 
\begin_inset Formula $q_{s},$
\end_inset

 the tangent space 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{q_{0}}\mathcal{C}$
\end_inset

 collapses to the pair of vectors 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ \pm\phi'\left(\theta_{s}\right)\sqrt{-\gamma\left(\theta_{s}\right)/\beta\left(\theta_{s}\right)}\right\} $
\end_inset

,
